BaT Auction: 1965 Bizzarrini Monoposto Prototype

This monoposto prototype was built by Bizzarrini S.p.A. in late 1965 for French businessman and racer Regis Fraissinet. It is said to have been retained by Bizzarrini until the 1970s and was imported to the US in the 1980s. It was acquired by the seller in 2005 and subsequently refurbished, with work completed in 2008 prior to the car being shown at the 2013 Concorso Italiano in Monterey, California. It is currently on loan to the National Corvette Museum in Bowling Green, Kentucky. The car features fiberglass bodywork finished in red over a tubular steel chassis, and power comes from a rebuilt 327ci Chevrolet V8 paired with a ZF five-speed manual gearbox. Features include a four-wheel independent suspension with Koni coilovers, four-wheel disc brakes with inboard rear units, quad Weber carburetors, “double-hump” cylinder heads, 15″ wheels with knock-off hubs, a fixed racing seat, a right-hand shifter, and a Personal wood-rimmed steering wheel. The car has not been run since 2008 according to the seller, and sorting will be required prior to use. This Bizzarrini is now offered in Bowling Green, Kentucky, on a bill of sale.

BaT Auction: Modified 1989 BMW M3

This 1989 BMW M3 is powered by a 2.3-liter S14 inline-four paired with a five-speed manual transmission and a limited-slip differential, and it is finished in Zinnoberrot over black Bison leather. The seller acquired the car in August 1999 and has subsequently added approximately 32k of the 110k miles shown. This E30 M3 is now offered with the owner’s manual, service records, spare parts, a tool kit, a Carfax report, and a Florida title in the seller’s name.
